2026-05-18 | Minimum Steps to Reach End

	Question
Return minimum steps needed to reach last index.
	Key Insight
This is a shortest path problem:
- indices = graph nodes  
- jumps = graph edges  
Since all moves cost 1:
		BFS gives shortest path.
Optimization:
After processing all equal-value jumps once,
clear them to avoid repeated traversals.
	Approach
1.	Store indices for every value:
		value → list of indices  
2.	Start BFS from index 0  
3.	For current index:
		try:
			i+1
			i-1
			all same-value indices
4.	Use visited array to avoid loops  
5.	After processing same-value group:
		clear its vector
		to avoid TLE
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int minJumps(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        if(n == 1)
            return 0;
        unordered_map<int, vector<int>> mp;
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            mp[arr[i]].push_back(i);
        }
        queue<pair<int,int>> q;
        vector<bool> vis(n, false);
        q.push({0, 0});
        vis[0] = true;
        while(!q.empty()){
            auto [idx, steps] = q.front();
            q.pop();
            if(idx == n - 1)
                return steps;
            // i-1
            if(idx - 1 >= 0 && !vis[idx - 1]){
                vis[idx - 1] = true;
                q.push({idx - 1, steps + 1});
            }
            // i+1
            if(idx + 1 < n && !vis[idx + 1]){
                vis[idx + 1] = true;
                q.push({idx + 1, steps + 1});
            }
            // same value jumps
            for(int next : mp[arr[idx]]){
                if(!vis[next]){
                    vis[next] = true;
                    q.push({next, steps + 1});
                }
            }
            // important optimization
            mp[arr[idx]].clear();
        }
        return -1;
    }
};
	Key Insight
BFS guarantees:
		first time reaching last index
		is minimum steps.  
Clearing processed equal-value groups
prevents repeated expensive traversals
and makes the solution efficient.
